<title>USA: Tobacco companies say agreement is a &quot;bitter pill&quot;.</title>
<headline>Tobacco companies say agreement is a &quot;bitter pill&quot;.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-06-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Major cigarette companies described the landmark agreement reached with U.S. states on Friday as a &quot;bitter pill&quot; but said they hoped the deal would lead to a new era of cooperation on tobacco issues.</p>
<p>&quot;The proposal is a bitter pill because our companies have made concessions that were extremely difficult,&quot; said Philip Morris Cos. Inc. Senior Vice President Steven Parrish, reading a statement on behalf of the tobacco industry. &quot;But on balance, this plan is preferable to a continuation of a decades-long controversy that has failed to produce a constructive outcome for anyone.&quot;</p>
</text>
